Problem 3

The dataset I chose to analyze in this problem is based on thousands of responses to given football scenarios. One example of the many different scenarios include: It is first down and 10. The ball is on your opponents 40 yardline. There is 3 seconds left in the second quarter. You are down by 3 points. Would you:

For each of the scenarios, there are five possible responses: kick a field goal, pass, run, dont know / it depends, kneel down, or punt. For each of the scenarios, respondents decided what play they would choose if they were the coach. The responses were gathered and are provided by https://www.crowdflower.com/data-for-everyone/.

Given the many different scenarios, I chose to look at portions of the scenarios that included whether it was first down and 10, the ball was on the opponents 20 yard line, there was three seconds left in the quarter, and the ball was on your 45 yard line. With the exception of the second and fourth portion, many of these overlap for multiple scenarios. Based on the word clouds and bar graphs, we can see that passing is certainly the most common choice if it is 1st and 10. When the ball is on the opponents 20 yard line, running the ball becomes the most popular while passing is a rather close second option. If there are three seconds left, passing is the most common selection by respondents, but kicking a field goal is not an uncommon selection in this scenario. Finally, for plays from your 45 yard line, running and passing are equally common selections. Dont know, kneel down and punt are always rare selections given these four scenarios.

url <- "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/stevewalsh124/STAT_5014/master/08_text_mining_Rnotebooks_bash_sed_awk/survey_data.txt"
survey_words <- read.delim(url, header = T, fill = T, stringsAsFactors = F)
# survey_words

text_df1 <- data_frame(line = 1:14, text = survey_words[, 1])
text_df2 <- data_frame(line = 1:14, text = survey_words[, 2])
text_df3 <- data_frame(line = 1:14, text = survey_words[, 3])
text_df4 <- data_frame(line = 1:14, text = survey_words[, 4])
text_df <- rbind(text_df1, text_df2, text_df3, text_df4)
# text_df

new_text <- text_df[, 2] %>% unnest_tokens(word, text)  #%>% count(word, sort = T)
# new_text
new_lower <- tolower(new_text)
# new_lower class(new_lower)

tidy_text <- new_lower %>% str_replace_all("ineer", "") %>% str_replace_all("eng", 
    "engineer") %>% str_replace_all("iate", "") %>% str_replace_all("ermed", 
    "") %>% str_replace_all("int", "intermediate") %>% str_replace_all("inner", 
    "") %>% str_replace_all("beg", "beginner") %>% str_replace_all("some", "") %>% 
    str_replace_all("just", "") %>% str_replace_all("teeny", "") %>% str_replace_all("amount", 
    "") %>% str_replace_all("of", "") %>% str_replace_all("surface", "") %>% 
    str_replace_all("and", "")


# (tidy_text)
tidy_df <- data_frame(text = tidy_text)
# tidy_df
finishedtext <- tidy_df %>% unnest_tokens(word, text) %>% count(word, sort = T)
# finishedtext

# new_text %>% anti_join(stop_words) %>% count(word, sort =T)

finishedtext %>% with(wordcloud(word, n, min.freq = 1, max.words = 1500, colors = brewer.pal(8, 
    "Dark2")))

finishedtext %>% mutate(word = reorder(word, n)) %>% ggplot(aes(word, n, fill = word)) + 
    geom_col() + xlab(NULL) + ylab("Frequencies") + coord_flip() + ggtitle("Most Frequent Responses in Programming Survey") + 
    scale_fill_manual(values = colorRampPalette(brewer.pal(8, "Accent"))(27))
